====Wrong bishop====
{{Main|Wrong bishop|Wrong rook pawn}}
In an [[chess endgame|endgame]] with a bishop, in some cases the bishop is the &quot;[[wrong bishop]]&quot;, meaning that it is on the wrong color of square for some purpose (usually [[promotion (chess)|promoting]] a pawn). For example, with just a bishop and a [[rook pawn]], if the bishop cannot control the promotion square of the pawn, it is said to be the &quot;wrong bishop&quot; or the pawn is said to be the [[wrong rook pawn]]. This results in some positions being [[draw (chess)|drawn]] (by setting up a [[fortress (chess)|fortress]]) which otherwise would be won.
